caption: We arrived at this spot for a meeting. This spot was recommended to us by a friend.  Well, it was a winning. the crew were so friendly and we felt good. The food was just great. We enjoyed every moment and we will definitely return to this restaurant. Keep it up.

Great food and atmosphere, as always. My average review stems from two things:  1.) Extremely slow service and general lack of attentiveness from the servers.  2.) Using a somewhat bizarre/inconsiderate tactic to increase sales on Valentines Day, which was to offer only one style of menu: a $79 per-person, multi-course meal. I understand that it’s a special day, but we (myself and the person I came with) simply wanted an entrée, which they were “unable to accommodate because it is [was] Valentines Day.” Instead, we had to order the works, running about $100 more than we budgeted for. The tactic here is extremely obvious and, frankly, disappointing.

If it was possible to give 0 stars that’s exactly what I would do. I made reservations to eat hear for my 32nd birthday. I was told if I had 12 guest it would be possible for me to eat in the regular dinning. The day before i was told i couldn’t reserve a regular dinning area, and the event coordinator that approved it didn’t realize the rules were changed. I was never notified of this change a head of time. Luckily once we arrived to the restaurant they accommodated my party size. Unfortunately that was the only good thing about this place. Appetizers took forever to come and it literally took 2 1/2  hrs for our main course to come. When we  asked to speak to the evening  manager about the extreme delay in service he responded rudely and dismissive. He even went as far as to walk away while we were talking.I asked for my birthday cake to be brought out because my guest were leaving due to the bad service. It took 30 mins for them to bring it out. The excuse was that they were trying to put candles on it...the cake came out with NO CANDLES!  I have received better customer service at Friday’s then here! Only once I became upset because my birthday dinner was a disaster did the manger change his tune. He gave an apology and made an excuse as to why he walked off on us. The manager adjusted the bill but my birthday dinner was already ruined and my guest were ready to leave. I was completely embarrassed and hurt that we were treated as if we were a burden or a waste of time. I sincerely hope that this restaurants evening staff learn to be considerate of others. I would not recommend coming here for any celebration. It’s not worth the money or time.

First I called early that afternoon and made our reservation we with someone named Dexter.  Who took all my information and told me the reservation was made. When I called back later to confirm I was told by a young woman that one had never been made and wasnt treated like I had even made one till i mentioned the young man's name. Once we arrived they were sat at a table with rose petals on the table, this would have been so lovely had most of the petals not been very wilted and the menu my boyfriend was given was covered in wine stains. Our waitress was very busy, we were told they were short staffed but with 4 other tables , we rarely saw her and it took an 30 mins to get our order taken. Honestly it felt like she was more concerned with tables where she thought the tips were at. Our drinks came out very late aswell which kinda made the wait twice as bother some.  A cocktail would have helped pass the time. We almost filled up on bread trying to make it till our appetizer arrived. The manager was running around making up for the slack to the point when we left we tried to tip her personally  aside from our waitress bcuz we thought she was the bar back. I also told my waitress which glass of wine I would like with my steak and she didnt bring it out till I was well into my steak. She took my plate before I was done eating and stuck another plate on top of my 59 dollars steak so quickly I had no time to ask for it back.  For the 230$ we spent on dinner , we expected much better service. I wouldn't recommend coming here bcuz of the fact the service didnt match the price thou the food was delicious. Simply disappointing!  I used to frequent Sullivan's in Baltimore annually for my birthday, but have not been there for a few years.  I was highly anticipating my return to one of my favorites for the atmosphere, the staff and the food!  Unfortunately things change and great things do not last forever, I was very disappointed with my most recent visit.  As soon as I walked in I knew things were different.  There was no crowd, this place used to be busy, even the bar was close to empty.  The house music, in my opinion, was terrible; Bing Crosby was playing, felt like a wake.  The music used to be upbeat, lively jazz fusion which created a great vibe throughout the restaurant, not old school yawn fest music like Bing Crosby.  Even the website talks about the music being lively with an unforgettable atmosphere, not this time.  And I guess there is no longer a dress code or at least a preferred attire policy.  Many patrons were in ordinary t-shirts with graphics and some had jeans low enough exposing their underwear, all the while being quite loud, even using a cell phone on speaker.  I felt like I was at a local fast food restaurant, certainly not at a steakhouse promising lively atmosphere and unforgettable experiences.  The meal and service were decent but nothing special, not like the many times I had visited before.  My steak was over-cooked as was the $60 1lb lobster tail.  The server never asked if entrees were cooked to our order nor if I would like any additional cocktails after my first.  One positive was the server being very attentive to our food allergies, which we greatly appreciated.  Also, we were disappointed there were no Gluten-Free options for desert, not even sorbet!  Many visits prior to this we would stay 2.5 - 3hrs and running up the tab to $300- $400 per couple, but this visit had me ready to leave after an hour and unfortunately feeling like I had severely over-paid for the experience we received.  Unfortunately we left deflated and extremely disappointed with our entire experience.

Arrived a half hour to closing tonight with 7 total adults.  Expected to have a server with an attitude and halfway decent food because of the late night visit and people wanting to go home. That was not the case. I ordered the cowboy steak.  The rest of my family ordered a mixed green salad, 2x sea bass, New York strip steak, and a filet mignon. Everything was cooked as requested. Sides were mashed potatoes, mac n cheese, and broccoli. Everything was absolutely fantastic.  I don't recall our servers name but he was great. He was patient and never gave us the stink-eye for making him stay late :) Desert was New York cheesecake and key lime pie; just as good as the rest of our dinner. This place does not skimp on details with your food. They strive for perfection.  None of us expected to have such a great dining experience.  It all started off with  simply finding something open late at night. Definitely coming back.

First time going we we're celebrating our anniversary. We were able to do a last minute reservation which was awesome. We opted to use valet parking. When we pulled up to valet the valet did not approach our vehicle. We put the window down to and stared at them with no assistance. We thought we had stopped at the wrong spot so after sitting there for 3 or 4 minutes without assistance we drove around the block pulled up again same person was there. We proceeded to get out of our car when he walked over to help us. We went inside to the check in desk which was empty.  Again not sure we were at the correct spot since it was in an odd location. We looked around for assistance while waiters walked past us without saying a single word. We finally grabbed one that had walked past us twice and asked if we were in the right place. He said he would get the girl who works the desk. Upon being seated we ended up with the same guy who found the front desk person as our waiter. He did not appear knowledgeable about the menu. We placed our orders and proceeded to wait while another couple came in their waiter told them all of the specials made recommendations etc. Their salad arrived all the while we were still waiting for ours and had arrived at least 20 minutes before them. We were about to find our waiter when he walks by nonchalantly sees that we never got our salads and brings them to us. He walks away ans comes back 2 minutes later and says apparently the kitchen is moving faster then usual and your food is already ready so you want it know or do u want to wait. Of course we asked for it immediately. Someone came to refill our waters and ran out of water at a half of glass instead of coming back to to it off he never came back. The food was another story. The cheese steak egg rolls we're the best thing I ever had in my life. I ordered a medium well steak which should have some pink and it was well done. The waiter never asked if it was okay nor did he come back to check on us until it was time for the check. Overall not a good experience. The next time I'll just do carryout for the eggrolls only. For the price our experience should have been much better.

Typical poor quality food and service that you will receive in Baltimore. Ate with group in the restaurant twice and then made the mistake of ordering a to-go dinner for our stay at the Hyatt Regency. The servers were a disappointment considering the relatively slow volume of customers. The to-go order was a disaster. There are better options in the area. The bisque and calamari are tasty.

I ordered my meal to go and was extremely disappointed. I was charged for a Filet Oscar, but received a sirloin. My other filet was ordered medium, but was cooked rare to the point I could not eat it. They did not include the sauce on the side.  The caesar salad did not include salad dressing. The first time eating at the restaurant was also disappointing. I ordered a filet medium, but it was burnt on the outside and well done on the inside. There are definitely better places to eat in Baltimore.

The atmosphere was louder than I expected, but fair for a Saturday night. I had reservation and there was no wait time which was a plus. The drinks were good and my favorite appetizer was the cheesesteak egg rolls.  It’s in an odd location if your not familiar with the area. I was confused trying to find parking and ended up at the lot connected to the resturaunt. It was scary walking through that alley to get to/from the resturaunt. Also, there was no lot attendant and I had to use my card to get out the exit. Ironically, my card didn’t work so we ended up using my husbands and the following week both of those cards were compromised. Please use caution.
Food was too salty

Took my wife here for date night on Saturday, 2/16/19.  We had been to the Sullivans in Omaha, NE, where we lived prior to moving to the Baltimore area, many times without incident.  It was our go to destination if we wanted a quality steak.  We had been to the Baltimore location on two prior dates and the experience was good, but not exceptional.  This last time was a disaster.  We had ordered the white cheddar au gratin potatoes, Brussels sprouts and a 16 oz. Ribeye, cooked to medium.  In addition, we had ordered salads, which were fine.  The steak had come out and was medium rare.  We requested the steak be sent back.  After about 10 minutes, our waiter brought the steak back.  It was STILL medium rare.  At that point, since we had cut into the steak multiple times, I had asked for them to simply start over with a new steak.  On the third try, it was ok.  It was very thin, compared to the one they had presented us with prior, and very salty.  But, my wife and I did manage to consume about 2/3 of it.  The au gratin potatoes were not cooked throughout.  They were very hard in the middle.  When we spoke to the manager about them, he said we were the third table to complain about them.  Thankfully the knockout martinis were good, and the best part of our meal.  In defense of the establishment, they did not charge us for our meal, only our drinks.  Regardless, we will not find ourselves coming back here again any time in the near future.  We'll continue to make Ruths Chris our go to while still in the area.

Lets see, Valet service good Bar service not bad Arrived early for reservation so we checked in and had a drink. Asked about our table twice while at the bar, then after 45 minutes we were told our table was given to anther party. Was offered drinks as compensation not bad but should not happen. There was something spilled on the on the floor next to the bar when we walked in, a wet floor sign was put up at some point. When we left nearly two hours later spill was still there. As we were leaving after a steak dinner that wasn't all that a rodent ran from the kitchen to the hostess stand. This establishment seamed poorly managed I will not go back.

Went here before a show to get happy hour prices. Prices were decent for an upscale bar downtown, food was really good, drink selection was also good, and the servers were all really friendly! We didn't sit in the restaurant side, just the bar, so I would recommend it if you are in the area looking for a bar to step into.

My husband and I come here every year to celebrate our wedding Anniversary. We always  brag about the service and food, however this was a huge disappointment. We always order the bone-in rib eye, well done. Our steak came out burnt, very crispy and black. Because we waited over 45 minutes for the steak we cut around the burnt surface. The crabcakes is another one of our regular choices, it was fried to hard and was not appetizing at all. This was a huge disappointment because we travel over 45 to an hour to visit this establishment each year and it really ruined our anniversary. Also, our waiter never mentioned our Anniversary until we asked for the check and bought us out a frozen slice of cheesecake that was just the icing on the cake! There is definitely a change in the food and service, and it's very disappointing because we started this tradition with your restaurant and now we don't know if we will return..

This was my first visit to Sullivan's and definitely my last.

This year was not as good as years past. After dinner, we asked for a Sullivan's coffee.  Our waiter kept laughing saying he hadn't heard any one ask for that for a long time, which I thought was rather strange. We got our coffee and mine was cold and my husband's was just lukewarm.  I mentioned to our waiter that I couldn't drink it because it was cold. He said yeah it's not on the menu anymore.  I told him I had no idea it wasn't, as he didn't mention that when we ordered them. He said he would take it off the check, which he didn't and we had to remind him to do so. We had our leftovers boxed up to go. When we got home, he didn't put my asparagus in the box. I had it all cut up on my plate ready to be boxed up. Last year everything was fine except the waiter spilled ice cold iced tea on me. Sat there in wet clothes eating my Turkey dinner. Think this will be the last time we go there. Time to look for another place.

Sat ourselves in the bar area due to 2 hr table wait. Our server was sparse in care. We were never asked for refills on drinks (until the end of course when we were probably looking real irritated.) and the food was just ok for the price. Took a total of 2 hrs from start to finish for our dining experience. Go somewhere else guys, it’s not worth it in the bar area at least. We waited over half an hr for a salad and some soup. And a steak that should’ve taken 10 min on the grill.

If I could give negative stars I would!!  We seated ourselves in the bar area where we waited 15minutes to have the one server come over to us; we asked for menus; she appeared miserable from the get-go. She didn’t even take a drink order.  We ordered a $45 dollar steak and a burger which we asked to be cooked well, well, well done.  As we waited for our food we noticed a chicken dish served raw to the table next to us (they comped that tables meal) and another table have there dinner served on three separate plates; each dish coming out in delayed succession and not together. The soup they ordered didn’t arrive and only did after they complained and said they would no longer like it.  Some of the food they ordered didn’t come out at all and the manager had to apologize that they no longer had it in stock. So they took there order, waited till the rest of the food was prepared then served what they had available. Only then telling them that there order would be incomplete.  When our food showed up the burger was raw and not cooked as requested. The $45 dollar steak came alone, on a plate with no vegetables, no compliments whatsoever.  The washrooms were in dire straights, the service scarce, the hospitality completely missing. I’ve never been to a $$$ steakhouse for a date night that turned out this miserable.  By the time our undercooked burger came back from the kitchen we had lost all appetite to eat or be in Sullivan’s any longer.  Save your money, time and sanity and head to the Rusty Scupper or Pratt Street Alehouse right down the street.

Sullivan's Steakhouse next to the Inner Harbor on The Charm'tastic Mile has an excellent prix fix menu that features a New York Strip that is full of flavor. The Fried calamari is a very appetizer as well. The wine and cocktail selections are very nice as well. The private rooms allow for a superb business dinner.

Terrible dinner in my opinion based on my groups experience. And so untypical of a Del Frisco group restaurant. We arrived with reservations and had to wait 22 minutes for a table. Why have reservations? Lukewarm steaks, grossly undercooked and even worse, served on cold plates. Seriously, $48 ribeye on a COLD plate? Ordered medium well and received a bleeding and bloody rare steak. Then the broccoli seemed to have either sand,dirt or some type ground gritty substance in it. It was not the kisher salt for sure.....We returned it out of fear for our health and requested they do an autopsy to determine what foreign substance may have been added to our broccoli. Very concerning and disturbing. Hours after dinner I was still feeling the grit between my teeth. Neglectful service from our waiter, probably because we were not ordering expensive wines or multiple cocktails to make us a larger ticket table. 2 managers stopped by and comped 1 steak but the dinner was still an epic fail. Money was not an issue.....we expected a high food quality meal, even with neglectful service.I am still very concerned and having anxiety about what foreign gritty substance was in that broccoli that I swallowed 2 bites of.....Sullivans never again for our group.

We just finished our meal at Sullivan’s, and the one word that could be used to describe it is mediocre. The entrance smelled of gas, and although it is due to the gas line on the street, isn’t the first thing I want to smell when I walk into a nice steakhouse. At 7:30 on a Saturday night, the restaurant wasn’t too crowded but it definitely filled up as the night went on. We ordered the calamari which we all really enjoyed. However, our waiter made a snarky comment about how fast we ate it. The comments kept coming during our soup course of lobster and shrimp bisque. At least the soup was good. For the main course, 2 of the 4 guests ordered the crab legs. The crab legs tasted fishy and didn’t have the same buttery taste like other king crab legs that they had had. I and another member ordered the NY strip from the price fixed dinner. The potatoes came with ham and we don’t eat ham (he brought over horseradish mashed potatoes, good thing I don’t like horseradish, but he did the right thing), and the steak was tougher than expected. We did also order Mac and cheese and that was the best thing of the night. For $10, it was a huge portion of mac plus it was my favorite pasta shape, shells. To end off the night, we had cheesecake and key lime pie and they were two full sized pieces even though they were the third course of the $44 dollar price fixed meal. The desserts were great. Although we didn’t love the steak, the price fixed meal is definitely the way to go.

Here's the lowdown, the food was very good (except the asparagus -that was bland. I didn't get the sauce-my server thought it was gross so he left it off, with out asking. He did send some home with and he's right-quite unpleasant) The atmosphere was clean, classy and well maintained. Our drinks we're good. Our service was-meh. Our server was engaging and had a good personality for the service industry. BUT the service was not fine dining. I have 24 years in fine dining My observations: The hostess was sloppy. She was wearing black leggings and dirty flats. She had a thin gray yoga t-shirt on and a sloppy cardigan over it. No make-up. She looked like she rolled out of bed. Her hair was unkempt and sloppy. And she was no welcoming or pleasant. Maybe she was having a bad day? You still have to at least put in an effort if you plan to work in the service industry. When I made my reservation, I specified that this was my husband's birthday and we had a sitter and would like a quiet table. She seated us in the middle of the restaurant, literally at a 4top. Like I said, our server was a nice guy. But he's not a fine dining server. Or maybe he just needs a little tweaking. He delivered our drinks and I had to wipe the outside of my glass because someone had spilled it down the outside of the glass. I put my dirty butter knife on my appetizer plate and he took it off and left it on the table for me to use again. Etiquette says he should remove all dirty flatware before the next course. I ran out of water, twice. My husband requested the course menu, he dropped it on the table instead of handing to him-my husband was taking a drink. See above asparagus incident. And he never offered us another drink. We decided to go somewhere else for coffee. The steak and calamari are amazing. My chicken was awesome. But I expected more in the way of service. If you're going to spend $150+ on dinner, you should have excellent service.
Good food good service.

The experience at Sullivan wasn't very nice it was a lovely place to go and have dinner for my anniversary the service was very good and the food was excellent I would advise anyone to go to Sullivan and have the experience of a lovely evening as I did

Food was excellent, 1st time in Baltimore, but had no trouble finding the restaurant. Parking is simple, garage across the street, and for lazy people like me, there's a valet right in front of restaurant. Although food was good, what set Sullivan apart was the service. The calamari appetizers were delicious.   Our steaks were very good...cooked to order...and the sides were more than enough....but we even had room for dessert.
